<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="53" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="18.[136,1089,980,1443]" pageId="18" pageNumber="53">
Taxonomic notes. Numerous subspecies of this externally strikingly variable species are described. The nominotypical subspecies is restricted to the eastern periphery of the Austrian Alps. Further subspecies occur in the Central and western Alps, and Alsace (
<taxonomicName authority="Schawerda, 1925" authorityName="Schawerda" authorityYear="1925" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Mamestra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="serratilinea" subSpecies="helvetica">
<emphasis box="[579,937,1081,1107]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="53">Mamestra serratilinea helvetica</emphasis>
Schawerda, 1925
</taxonomicName>
), Balkan peninsula (
<taxonomicName authority="Drenovsky, 1931" authorityName="Drenovsky" authorityYear="1931" box="[451,1008,1114,1140]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="53" phylum="Nemertea" rank="subSpecies" species="serratilinea" subSpecies="kowatschevi">
<emphasis box="[451,788,1114,1140]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="53">Polia serratilinea kowatschevi</emphasis>
Drenovsky, 1931
</taxonomicName>
), Central 
<collectingCountry box="[183,290,1148,1174]" name="Turkey" pageId="18" pageNumber="53">Anatolia</collectingCountry>
(
<taxonomicName authority="Varga, 1974" authorityName="Varga" authorityYear="1974" box="[305,733,1148,1174]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="53" phylum="Nemertea" rank="subSpecies" species="serratilinea" subSpecies="pinkeri">
<emphasis box="[305,581,1148,1174]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="53">Polia serratilinea pinkeri</emphasis>
Varga, 1974
</taxonomicName>
), and more clearly differentiated in Central Asia (
<taxonomicName authority="(Alpheraky, 1887)" baseAuthorityName="Alpheraky" baseAuthorityYear="1887" box="[401,906,1181,1208]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="53" phylum="Nemertea" rank="subSpecies" species="serratilinea" subSpecies="spalax">
<emphasis box="[401,674,1181,1207]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="53">Polia serratilinea spalax</emphasis>
(Alphéraky, 1887)
</taxonomicName>
, in the Hindukush-Himalaya area (
<taxonomicName authority="Hacker et Weigert, 1990" authorityName="Hacker et Weigert" authorityYear="1990" box="[402,1028,1215,1242]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="53" phylum="Nemertea" rank="subSpecies" species="serratilinea" subSpecies="tenebricosa">
<emphasis box="[402,725,1215,1241]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="53">Polia serratilinea tenebricosa</emphasis>
Hacker et Weigert, 1990
</taxonomicName>
), but also in western 
<collectingCountry box="[329,448,1249,1275]" name="Mongolia" pageId="18" pageNumber="53">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
(
<taxonomicName authority="Varga, 1974" authorityName="Varga" authorityYear="1974" box="[464,945,1249,1275]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="53" phylum="Nemertea" rank="subSpecies" species="serratilinea" subSpecies="eremorealis">
<emphasis box="[464,792,1249,1275]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="53">Polia serratilinea eremorealis</emphasis>
Varga, 1974
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[136,1089,980,1443]" pageId="18" pageNumber="53">
This species shows some convergence to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="McCabe" authorityYear="1980" box="[703,835,1282,1308]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="53" phylum="Nemertea" rank="species" species="propodea">
<emphasis box="[703,835,1282,1308]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="53">P. propodea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the bifid terminal part of the right saccular process.The two lineages are, however, rather distant by their CO1 sequences. The asymmetrisation of the clavus and saccular processes show an evident geographical variation; its analysis and taxonomic interpretation will be treated in a further publication.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
